  "texts": [
    "We subsequently train the model on smaller labeled datasets depicting various medical and clinical tasks, allowing it to learn to use its internalized medical knowledge for tasks such as diagnosing diseases, interpreting medical literature, and understanding patient cases.",
    "To further enhance the model's reasoning abilities when it makes predictions, we use the chain-of-thought [15] and self-consistency [16] prompting techniques, which encourage MEDITRON to \"think aloud\" by generating multiple intermediate reasoning arguments before reaching a conclusion.",
    "These approaches substantially improve MED-ITRON's performance on medical benchmarks and expose a more transparent and interpretable decision-making process to medical professionals.",
    "Enhancing MEDITRON with image understandingLarge multimodal models are extensions of language models that can generate natural language responses from image input and text prompts [32,33].",
    "Visual perception enables models to handle more general and expressive medical applications in modalities beyond text, such as X-ray, CT, and MRI."
  ],
